pr_review_comment_body:
This test suite can be rewritten with some neat pytest-flask features:

- Pass options via [`pytest.mark.options` decorator](http://pytest-flask.readthedocs.org/en/latest/features.html#pytest-mark-options-pass-options-to-your-application-config)

- No need to initialize extension explicitly, it will be initialized by `pytest` during resolving fixture

- Refine test suite, e.g. split test suites into different functions (one test per feature) and move them into separate namespace for better readability

This test suite looks good for me:

```python
@pytest.mark.usefixtures('app')
class TestUTC:

    @pytest.mark.options(humanize_use_utc=True)
    def test_use_utc(self, h):
        assert humanize.time._now == datetime.utcnow

    @pytest.mark.options(humanize_use_utc=False)
    def test_dont_use_utc(self, h):
        assert humanize.time._now == datetime.now

    @pytest.mark.options(humanize_use_utc=True)
    def test_naturaltime_with_utc(self, h):
        assert h._humanize(datetime.utcnow()) == 'now'
```

You can simply say

return list(neuron.soma for neuron in neurons)

instead of repeatedly appending to a list

I think it would be clearer to write:

```python
data = {
    'client_id': self.client_id,
    'secret': self.secret,
    'public_token': public_token,
}
if account_id is not None:
    data['account_id'] = account_id
```

Nitpick: Rather than copy the dictionary, this can be written more expressively as a dictionary comprehension:

```python
            params = resolve_params(obj, self.related_url_kwargs, default=self.default)
            non_null_params = {
                key: value for key, value in params.items()
                if value is not None
            }
            if non_null_params:
                return self.related_url.format(**non_null_params)
```

Thanks for pointing that I out. I didn't realize it had a property already. Could you add the following code to this function then?

```
    NT_ASSERT(otCtx);
    PMS_FILTER pFilter = otCtxToFilter(otCtx);
    NTSTATUS status;

    // Indicate to the miniport
    status =
        otLwfCmdSetProp(
            pFilter,
            SPINEL_PROP_PHY_TX_POWER,
            SPINEL_DATATYPE_INT8_S,
            aPower
        );
    if (!NT_SUCCESS(status))
    {
        LogError(DRIVER_DEFAULT, "Set SPINEL_PROP_PHY_TX_POWER failed, %!STATUS!", status);
    }
```
